description:
As the Children of Israel continued their journey, they unfortunately encountered many challenges. God led them to Kadesh Barnea, where Moses sent 12 spies into the land. Two of the spies, Joshua and Caleb reported back and said that the land could be their new home. However, the Children of Israel did not believe them. So near but so far, a common phrase today, that applies to the journey of the Israelites from Egypt to Canaan. A journey that should have taken just under 2 weeks took 40 years!
